<法規>
<法規性質>命令</法規性質>
<英文法規名稱>Regulations of consolidated donation</英文法規名稱>
<中文法規名稱>統一捐募運動辦法</中文法規名稱>
<法規網址>http://law.moj.gov.tw/Eng/LawClass/LawContent.aspx?PCODE=D0050007</法規網址>
<最新英文異動日期>20070119</最新英文異動日期>
<廢止註記>廢</廢止註記>
<沿革內容><![CDATA[1. Enacted and promulgated on May 2, 1942 by KMT Government.
2. Revised and promulgated as decree Tai Kuei Tzu No. 2873 of The Executive Yuan No. 42 on May 20, 1953
3. Abolished on January 19, 2007]]></沿革內容>
<法規內容>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 1</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[Donation for national defense construction, army gifts, charity cause and edbiz should be handled in accordance with these regulations.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 2</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[Donation for nationwide purpose may be collected from home and abroad, donation for purpose of a district should be collected only in the area of the district, but donation for relieving the people in disaster is not subject to these limits.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 3</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The purposes and methods of all kinds of donations should be reported to the relevant administrative authorities and enterprise competent authorities for approval, donations from abroad should be reported to the Executive Yuan for approval, donations without approval of the Executive Yuan should be banned.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 4</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The methods of donation should be in accordance with the following prescriptions:
1. Respect the liberty of donators, no apportion and prescribed amount or proportion are allowed.
2. No interruption to the traffic, no compulsory donation.
3. Sales of work should be made publicly and should not be forced to buyers.
4. The temporary receipts for persuading donation should be numbered and sealed by the donation organizing group, the par value of temporary receipts should not be rebated.
5. Donation organizer should not be paid, and the expenditure in the course of donation should be thrifty: the expenditure should be less than 5 percent of the amount of donation when the donation is less than NTD 50,000, and should be less than 2 percent when the donation is more than NTD 50,000.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 5</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[Donators should be subject to the following restrictions:
1. Prefects could not give donation to their own families.
2. Administrants could not persuade donation from people they administer. 
3. Schools could not persuade donation from students.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 6</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[Dominators (except for managers of nongovernmental enterprises) should not donate with non-private property.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 7</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[If a proportion of the donation should be borne by public fund, the government of all levels should order the one-off payment with public fund, but the authorities could not give donations in the name of the authorities.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 8</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The relevant administrative authorities should send personnel to check the implementation of donation activities, personnel in charge of the donation who violate the relevant decrees should be interdicted, those who commit crimes should be punished in accordance with the relevant act.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 9</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The income and expenditures of nationwide donation should be handled in accordance with National Treasury Act and the Regulations of the income and expenditures of consolidated donations, the income and expenditures of local donation should be handled in accordance with decisions by the local fisc competent authorities, administrative authorities and the enterprise competent authorities.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 10</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[These regulations should be put into implementation as of the date of promulgation.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
</法規內容>
</法規>
